@startuml
' Sequence diagram for the Netty private-protocol round-trip example.
' Focus: NettyClient + NettyServer pipeline workflow, covering the
'   - LengthFieldBasedFrameDecoder + Marshalling decode of the Header/attachment/body
'   - login handshake (LOGIN_REQ <-> LOGIN_RESP, server-side whitelist + dedup)
'   - heartbeat scheduled task on the client (every 5s) and server reply
'   - ReadTimeoutHandler (50s) -> exceptionCaught -> reconnect
' The wire format is the NettyMessage with Header (crcCode, length, sessionId,
' type, priority, attachment Map<String,Object>, body) marshalled with
' org.jboss.marshalling "serial" v5.
'
' Render with a PlantUML IDE plugin, the PlantUML CLI, or
' https://www.plantuml.com/plantuml/uml/.

title Netty Private Protocol Round-Trip: NettyClient <-> NettyServer (login + heartbeat)

skinparam maxMessageSize 0
skinparam BoxPadding 6
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
autonumber

actor "User\n(JVM)" as U

box "NettyClient\n(NioSocketChannel + ChannelPipeline)" #E3F2FD
    participant "NettyClient\nmain" as ClientMain
    participant "NettyMessageDecoder\nLengthFieldBasedFrameDecoder\n(maxFrame=1MB,\n lengthFieldOffset=4,\n lengthFieldLength=4,\n lengthAdjustment=-8,\n initialBytesToStrip=0)\n+ MarshallingDecoder" as CDec
    participant "NettyMessageEncoder\nMessageToMessageEncoder\n+ MarshallingEncoder" as CEnc
    participant "ReadTimeoutHandler\n(50s)" as CRTimeout
    participant "LoginAuthReqHandler\nChannelInboundHandlerAdapter" as CLogin
    participant "HeartBeatReqHandler\nChannelInboundHandlerAdapter\n+ ScheduledFuture(5s)" as CHeart
end box

box "Network (TCP 127.0.0.1:8080)" #F5F5F5
    participant "Socket" as Net
end box

box "NettyServer\n(NioServerSocketChannel + ChannelPipeline)" #E8F5E9
    participant "NettyServer\nmain" as ServerMain
    participant "NettyMessageDecoder\n(same params)\n+ MarshallingDecoder" as SDec
    participant "NettyMessageEncoder\n+ MarshallingEncoder" as SEnc
    participant "ReadTimeoutHandler\n(50s)" as SRTimeout
    participant "LoginAuthRespHandler\nChannelInboundHandlerAdapter\n(nodeCheck Map, whiteList)" as SLogin
    participant "HeartBeatRespHandler\nChannelInboundHandlerAdapter" as SHeart
end box

== 1. Server bootstrap ==

U -> ServerMain : main()
activate ServerMain #B5E5C1
ServerMain -> ServerMain : bind()\n  boss + worker =\n  MultiThreadIoEventLoopGroup(NioIoHandler.newFactory())\n  ServerBootstrap.channel(NioServerSocketChannel)\n  .option(SO_BACKLOG, 100)\n  .handler(LoggingHandler(INFO))
note right of ServerMain
  Server child pipeline (addLast order):
    1. NettyMessageDecoder(1MB, 4, 4, -8, 0)
    2. NettyMessageEncoder
    3. ReadTimeoutHandler(50)        (inbound, fires ReadTimeoutException)
    4. LoginAuthRespHandler           (inbound, accepts LOGIN_REQ)
    5. HeartBeatRespHandler           (inbound, accepts HEARTBEAT_REQ)
end note
ServerMain -> Net : bind(127.0.0.1, 8080).sync()
Net --> ServerMain : bound; log "Netty server start ok"
deactivate ServerMain

== 2. Client connect + pipeline init ==

U -> ClientMain : main()
activate ClientMain #B5E5C1
ClientMain -> ClientMain : connect(8080, "127.0.0.1")\n  group = MultiThreadIoEventLoopGroup(NioIoHandler.newFactory())\n  Bootstrap.channel(NioSocketChannel)\n  .option(TCP_NODELAY, true)
note right of ClientMain
  Client pipeline (addLast order):
    1. NettyMessageDecoder(1MB, 4, 4, -8, 0)
    2. NettyMessageEncoder
    3. ReadTimeoutHandler(50)
    4. LoginAuthReqHandler    (channelActive -> send LOGIN_REQ)
    5. HeartBeatReqHandler    (on LOGIN_RESP -> schedule heartbeat)
end note
ClientMain -> Net : connect(host, port).sync()
Net --> ClientMain : connected; closeFuture.sync() blocks
deactivate ClientMain

== 3. Login handshake (inbound channelActive triggers LOGIN_REQ) ==

ClientMain -> CLogin : channelActive(ctx)\n(channel becomes writable)
activate CLogin #FFE0B2
CLogin -> CLogin : buildLoginReq()\n  NettyMessage[header.type=LOGIN_REQ(3), body=null]
CLogin -> CEnc : writeAndFlush(NettyMessage)
activate CEnc
CEnc -> CEnc : encode(ctx, msg, out)\n  if (msg==null || header==null) throw\n  sendBuf = Unpooled.buffer()\n  writeInt(crcCode 0xabef0101)\n  writeInt(length placeholder 0)\n  writeLong(sessionId)\n  writeByte(type)  writeByte(priority)\n  writeInt(attachment.size)\n  for each entry: writeInt(keyLen) + writeBytes(UTF-8 key)\n               + MarshallingEncoder.encode(value,\n                  4-byte length placeholder + marshalled bytes)\n  body != null -> MarshallingEncoder.encode(body)\n  body == null -> writeInt(0)\n  sendBuf.setInt(4, sendBuf.readableBytes())   backpatch length
CEnc -> Net : ByteBuf (TCP bytes)
deactivate CEnc
deactivate CLogin

Net -> SDec : bytes (frame length prefixed)
activate SDec
SDec -> SDec : super.decode(ctx, in)\n  LengthFieldBasedFrameDecoder reads length @offset 4,\n  adjusts by -8 (length includes crcCode + lengthField),\n  returns the full frame (no strip)
SDec -> SDec : read frame -> Header\n  crcCode=readInt, length=readInt,\n  sessionId=readLong, type=readByte, priority=readByte\n  size=readInt; for i in size:\n    keyLen=readInt, key=readBytes(UTF-8),\n    attachment.put(key, MarshallingDecoder.decode(frame))\n  if readable>4: body=MarshallingDecoder.decode(frame)\n  else body=null
SDec -> SRTimeout : channelRead(NettyMessage)
deactivate SDec
activate SRTimeout
SRTimeout -> SLogin : channelRead(NettyMessage)\n  (ReadTimeoutHandler passes through unless timer fires)
deactivate SRTimeout
activate SLogin #C8E6C9
SLogin -> SLogin : type == LOGIN_REQ\n  nodeIndex = channel.remoteAddress().toString()
alt node already in nodeCheck
    SLogin -> SLogin : buildResponse(-1)   duplicate login
else new node
    SLogin -> SLogin : ip = ((InetSocketAddress) remoteAddress).getAddress().getHostAddress()\n    isOk = whiteList.contains(ip)   whitelist [127.0.0.1, 192.168.1.104]
    alt isOk
        SLogin -> SLogin : nodeCheck.put(nodeIndex, true)\n        buildResponse((byte) 0)
    else !isOk
        SLogin -> SLogin : buildResponse(-1)   not whitelisted
    end
end
SLogin -> SEnc : writeAndFlush(loginResp)\n  NettyMessage[header.type=LOGIN_RESP(4), body=byte result]
activate SEnc
SEnc -> Net : ByteBuf (TCP bytes)
deactivate SEnc
deactivate SLogin

Net -> CDec : bytes
activate CDec
CDec -> CDec : super.decode + read Header + attachment + body\n  (same path as server)
CDec -> CRTimeout : channelRead(NettyMessage)
deactivate CDec
activate CRTimeout
CRTimeout -> CLogin : channelRead(NettyMessage)
deactivate CRTimeout
activate CLogin #FFE0B2
CLogin -> CLogin : type == LOGIN_RESP\n  loginResult = (byte) message.getBody()
alt loginResult != 0
    CLogin -> Net : ctx.close()   login refused
else loginResult == 0
    CLogin -> CLogin : log.info("Login is ok", message)\n  ctx.fireChannelRead(msg)   pass downstream
    CLogin -> CHeart : channelRead(NettyMessage)
    activate CHeart #FFE0B2
    CHeart -> CHeart : type == LOGIN_RESP\n  heartBeat = ctx.executor().scheduleAtFixedRate(\n      HeartBeatTask(ctx), 0, 5, SECONDS)\n  (passes non-HEARTBEAT_RESP messages via fireChannelRead)
    deactivate CHeart
end
deactivate CLogin

== 4. Heartbeat loop (every 5s, client -> server -> client) ==

loop every 5s while channel is open
    CHeart -> CHeart : HeartBeatTask.run()\n  buildHeartBeat() -> NettyMessage[\n      header.type=HEARTBEAT_REQ(5), body=null]
    activate CHeart #FFE0B2
    CHeart -> CEnc : writeAndFlush(heartBeat)
    activate CEnc
    CEnc -> CEnc : encode (header only + body=0 sentinel)\n  attachment empty -> writeInt(0); body null -> writeInt(0)
    CEnc -> Net : ByteBuf
    deactivate CEnc

    Net -> SDec : bytes
    activate SDec
    SDec -> SDec : decode -> NettyMessage
    SDec -> SRTimeout : channelRead
    deactivate SDec
    activate SRTimeout
    SRTimeout -> SHeart : channelRead(NettyMessage)
    deactivate SRTimeout
    activate SHeart #C8E6C9
    SHeart -> SHeart : type == HEARTBEAT_REQ\n  log "Receive client heart beat message"\n  buildHeartBeat() -> NettyMessage[\n      header.type=HEARTBEAT_RESP(6), body=null]
    SHeart -> SEnc : writeAndFlush(heartBeat)
    activate SEnc
    SEnc -> Net : ByteBuf
    deactivate SEnc
    deactivate SHeart

    Net -> CDec : bytes
    activate CDec
    CDec -> CDec : decode -> NettyMessage
    CDec -> CRTimeout : channelRead
    deactivate CDec
    activate CRTimeout
    CRTimeout -> CLogin : channelRead(NettyMessage)\n  (LoginAuthReqHandler: not LOGIN_RESP -> fireChannelRead)
    deactivate CRTimeout
    activate CLogin #FFE0B2
    CLogin -> CHeart : fireChannelRead(msg)
    deactivate CLogin
    activate CHeart #FFE0B2
    CHeart -> CHeart : type == HEARTBEAT_RESP\n  log "Client receive server heart beat message"
    deactivate CHeart
end

== 5. ReadTimeoutHandler fires (50s of silence) ==

alt server-side silence > 50s (client ReadTimeoutHandler fires)
    CRTimeout -> CLogin : exceptionCaught(ctx,\n  ReadTimeoutException)
    activate CLogin #FFE0B2
    CLogin -> CLogin : exceptionCaught ->\n  ctx.fireExceptionCaught(cause)   pass to next handler
    note right of CHeart #FFE0E0
      HeartBeatReqHandler.exceptionCaught:
        heartBeat.cancel(true);
        heartBeat = null;
        ctx.fireExceptionCaught(cause);
      ScheduledFuture is cancelled so the 5s task stops.
    end note
    CLogin -> CHeart : fireExceptionCaught(cause)
    deactivate CLogin
    activate CHeart #FFE0B2
    CHeart -> CHeart : heartBeat.cancel(true); heartBeat=null;\n  ctx.fireExceptionCaught(cause)
    deactivate CHeart
end

alt server-side ReadTimeoutHandler fires (>50s no inbound)
    SRTimeout -> SLogin : exceptionCaught(ctx, ReadTimeoutException)
    activate SLogin #FFE0E0
    SLogin -> SLogin : nodeCheck.remove(remoteAddress)\n  ctx.close(); ctx.fireExceptionCaught(cause)
    deactivate SLogin
end

== 6. Channel close + client reconnect ==

Net -> ClientMain : closeFuture.sync() returns
activate ClientMain #B5E5C1
ClientMain -> ClientMain : finally block\n  executor.execute(runnable):\n    sleep(5s) -> connect(8080, "127.0.0.1")   re-bootstrap + reconnect
note right of ClientMain #FFF9C4
  Reconnect path:
    - new NioSocketChannel + fresh pipeline
    - channelActive -> LoginAuthReqHandler sends LOGIN_REQ again
    - On LOGIN_RESP(0) -> HeartBeatReqHandler schedules a new 5s task
    - Node-check dedup on server uses remoteAddress string; a reconnected
      socket from the same host:port reuses the entry if previously cleared
      on exceptionCaught, otherwise LoginAuthRespHandler returns -1.
end note
deactivate ClientMain

== 7. Exception paths ==

note over SLogin #FFE0E0
  LoginAuthRespHandler.exceptionCaught(ctx, cause):
    nodeCheck.remove(ctx.channel().remoteAddress().toString());
    ctx.close();
    ctx.fireExceptionCaught(cause);
  Triggers:
    - ReadTimeoutException after 50s of silence on the server side
    - I/O error on the channel
    - decoder throws (frame > 1MB -> TooLongFrameException,
      or marshalling failure / crcCode mismatch reading)
end note

note over CLogin #FFE0E0
  LoginAuthReqHandler.exceptionCaught(ctx, cause):
    ctx.fireExceptionCaught(cause);
  Login refused (loginResult != 0):
    ctx.close();   channel tears down, triggers reconnect in finally
end note

note over CDec, SDec #FFE0E0
  Wire format recap (NettyMessageEncoder):
    [crcCode:int] [length:int] [sessionId:long] [type:byte]
    [priority:byte] [attachment.size:int]
    for each attachment:
      [keyLen:int] [keyBytes(UTF-8)] [marshalledValue with 4-byte length prefix]
    body != null -> [marshalledBody with 4-byte length prefix]
    body == null -> [0:int]   4-byte zero sentinel, NOT a marshalled 0
  length field is backpatched via sendBuf.setInt(4, readableBytes())
  to cover crcCode + length + sessionId + type + priority + attachments + body.
end note

note over CHeart #FFF9C4
  Heartbeat is one-way request with response; if the server's
  HeartBeatRespHandler is removed or mis-wired the client still logs
  "send heart beat" every 5s but never sees HEARTBEAT_RESP, so
  ReadTimeoutHandler(50s) eventually fires -> reconnect.
end note

@enduml
